From 852d8aafdda733738b89b8646d3b3c53dc3db5c6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Adam (via Claude)" <adam@nexasec.local>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 07:20:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] M2: per-clip transcription (clip transcribe / transcribe-all)

- New services/clip_transcriber.py: resolves a clip's own attached
  audio, runs WhisperX, writes to sources/clips/<clip>/captions/raw/,
  updates clip status to 'transcribed'
- 'nexasec clip transcribe <project> <clip>' and
  'nexasec clip transcribe-all <project>' (skips clips with no audio
  attached rather than erroring, since a project can mix in-progress
  and ready clips)
- Emptied out the old commands/captions.py 'generate' command, which
  hardcoded the pre-M1 single-source path (assets/audio/source.wav)
  and no longer matched the clip-based layout. Reserved for the real
  Caption Engine in M4 (Arabic correction, RTL/LTR, styles, SRT/ASS
  export) built on top of these raw transcripts.
- Added pytest as a proper uv dev dependency (dependency-groups.dev)
  so 'uv sync' installs it automatically
- 5 new tests for transcription orchestration (path resolution,
  status updates, batch skip-logic), stubbing the WhisperX call
  itself so these don't require a GPU to run -- 22 tests total, all
  passing
